<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Flashcards</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/deployer/mottzi.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/mistexamples.css">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
</head>
<body>
    <main class="container">
        <a href="/MistExamples" class="back-link">← Back to Examples</a>
        <header class="mb-4">
            <span class="badge header-badge">InstanceComponent</span>
            <h1 class="m-0">Flashcards</h1>
            <p class="desc">Tied to database rows; re-renders automatically when Mist detects Fluent create, update, or delete events. This example tracks two models per card. It demonstrates Actions for database mutations (shuffling, deleting) which sync globally, and per-client <code>ComponentState</code> (flipping the card) which only re-renders for the acting client.</p>
        </header>
        #extend("FlashcardExample/FlashcardCreateComponent")
        <div class="flashcard-grid" mist-container="FlashcardComponent">
            #for(context in contexts):
                #extend("FlashcardExample/FlashcardComponent")
            #endfor
        </div>
    </main>
    <script src="/morphdom.js"></script>
    <script src="/mist.js"></script>
</body>
</html>